The paper discusses a method for training Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to add new capabilities while preserving existing ones, without access to the original training data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for training CNNs, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
